description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;West &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hertfordshire Hospitals NHS Trust is seeking a competent and committed Telecommunications Manager work within the ICT department, to design and support the delivery of telephony services across the Trust, on a 6-month fixed term contract.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Reporting to the Head of Technical Services you will be responsible for the telecommunications infrastructure and associated transformation plans for the telephony and bleep platforms. You will work with Trust ICT Infrastructure partners to ensure the availability, integrity, performance and security of the Trust telecommunications is maintained across multiple infrastructure components and meets service level agreements/contracted outcomes. In addition, you will help to set the ICT Technical Strategy, aligned to the Digital Strategy of the Trust. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To be successful in this role you will have a technical background with experience of working with voice management architectures, technologies and standards&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;and associated supporting infrastructure within large corporate environments. You will also be proficient in identifying and documenting technical requirements for a particular IT solution.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Jo Brown, Head of ICT Technical Services on 01442 287457&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
